'''Alcides Mendoza Castro''' (March 14, 1928 &ndash; June 20, 2012) was the [[Roman Catholic]] archbishop of the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Cuzco]], [[Peru]].

Ordained to the priesthood in 1951, he was named bishop in 1958 and in 1983 was named Archbishop of the Cuzco Archdiocese; he retired in 2003.<ref>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bmencas.html Alcides Mendoza Castro]</ref>

