This article lists the '''longest church buildings in the world''' as measured by various criteria.
==Scope== The term ''[[wiktionary:church|church]]'' is open to interpretation and debate. However, for the purposes of this article, it will be used to mean any [[church (building)|building]] which was built for the primary purpose of Christian worship, for any recognised denomination of Christianity. This includes all [[cathedral]]s (the seat of a [[bishop]]), [[basilica]]s, and other types of churches. It does '''not''' include temples of other religions, e.g. [[mosque]]s, [[synagogue]]s. It does include at least one building, [[Hagia Sophia]], which was built as a church but later became a mosque (and is now a museum).
