The '''Society for the Study of Christian Ethics''' ('''SSCE''') is an [[academic society]] in the [[United Kingdom]] for [[scholar]]s and [[wikt:practitioner|practitioner]]s whose work relates to [[theology|theological]] [[ethics]] and the fields of ethics, [[politics]], [[religion]], [[philosophy]], theology, and public life. It is a not-for-profit member association, serving as a professional and learned society for scholars involved in the academic study of [[Christian ethics]]. It draws members principally from across the UK but also [[Europe]], [[Asia]], and the [[Americas]].
The SSCE hosts an annual conference every September and a postgraduate conference every April.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ssce.org.uk/conferences|title=The SSCE Annual Conference {{!}} SSCE Membership and Conferences|website=www.ssce.org.uk|language=en|access-date=2018-05-29}}</ref> The current president (2014–2018) is [https://www.chester.ac.uk/departments/trs/staff/clough David Clough].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ssce.org.uk/committee|title=SSCE Committee {{!}} SSCE Membership and Conferences|website=www.ssce.org.uk|language=en|access-date=2018-05-29}}</ref> The SSCE has its own journal, ''[[Studies in Christian Ethics]]'', published by [[SAGE Publications]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ssce.org.uk/|title=SSCE Membership and Conferences|website=www.ssce.org.uk|language=en|access-date=2018-05-29}}</ref>
